n  \"capabilityMatrixPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json\",\n  \"capabilityMatrixDocPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md\",\n  \"runtimeCapabilityResolver\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\",\n  \"reducerScriptPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\",\n  \"pauseSentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n  \"archiveRoot\": \"research_archive\",\n  \"migrationWindowDays\": 28,\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n    \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"research/research.md\": \"mutable\"\n  },\n  \"_optimizerManaged\": {\n    \"description\": \"Fields managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). See optimizer-manifest.json for the canonical tunable/locked field registry.\",\n    \"manifestPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json\",\n    \"tunableFields\": [\"convergenceThreshold\", \"stuckThreshold\", \"maxIterations\"],\n    \"lockedFields\": [\"lineage\", \"reducer\", \"fileProtection\", \"sessionId\", \"status\"],\n    \"promotionMode\": \"advisory-only\"\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":77,"totalLines":77,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json","time":{"start":1781518687628,"end":1781518687637}},"id":"prt_ecac9d9b2001S2Y5EiJTYPdKfW","sessionID":"ses_13537258affeVXgYvTahskeLzp","messageID":"msg_ecac9cc17001wsnCUXc5D1JTib"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781518688514,"sessionID":"ses_13537258affeVXgYvTahskeLzp","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"tool_F21vAgyUeufuQ5DeOicg9aE6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Strategy Template\n3: description: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep research strategy\"\n6:   - \"research strategy template\"\n7:   - \"research session tracking\"\n8:   - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n9:   - \"research stop conditions\"\n10:   - \"ruled out research directions\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: planning\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n16: \n17: Runtime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n18: \n19: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n20: \n21: ### Purpose\n22: \n23: Serves as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n24: \n25: ### Usage\n26: \n27: - **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\n28: - **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, ruled-out directions, and Next Focus.\n29: - **Mutability:** Mutable — analyst-owned sections remain stable, while machine-owned sections are rewritten by the reducer after each iteration.\n30: - **Protection:** Shared state with explicit ownership boundaries. Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## 2. TOPIC\n35: [Research topic from config -- set during initialization]\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n40: - [ ] [Question 1 -- identified during initialization or iteration 1]\n41: - [ ] [Question 2]\n42: - [ ] [Question 3]\n43: \n44: ---\n45: \n46: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n47: [What this research session is NOT trying to answer -- populated during initialization]\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n52: [Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n57: [None yet -- populated as iterations answer questions]\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n62: ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n63: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n64: - [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n69: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n70: - [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n75: [Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n76: \n77: ### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n78: - What was tried: [specific approaches attempted]\n79: - Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n80: - Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n81: \n82: ### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n83: - What worked: [successful approaches in this category]\n84: - Prefer for: [related questions where this category may help]\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n89: [Approaches that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n90: - [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n91: \n92: ---\n93: \n94: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n95: [Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration]\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n100: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n101: [Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n106: - Max iterations: [from config]\n107: - Convergence threshold: [from config]\n108: - Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n109: - Progressive synthesis: true (default)\n110: - research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n111: - Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n112: - Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11\n113: - Canonical pause sentinel: `research/.deep-research-pause`\n114: - Capability matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n115: - Capability matrix doc: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n116: - Capability resolver: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`\n117: - Current generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n118: - Started: [timestamp]\n\n(End of file - total 118 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research strategy\"\n  - \"research strategy template\"\n  - \"research session tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n  - \"research stop conditions\"\n  - \"ruled out research directions\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research strategy\"\n  - \"research strategy template\"\n  - \"research session tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n  - \"research stop conditions\"\n  - \"ruled out research directions\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nServes as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\n- **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, ruled-out directions, and Next Focus.\n- **Mutability:** Mutable — analyst-owned sections remain stable, while machine-owned sections are rewritten by the reducer after each iteration.\n- **Protection:** Shared state with explicit ownership boundaries. Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n\n---\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n[Research topic from config -- set during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n- [ ] [Question 1 -- identified during initialization or iteration 1]\n- [ ] [Question 2]\n- [ ] [Question 3]\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n[What this research session is NOT trying to answer -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n[Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n[None yet -- populated as iterations answer questions]\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n\n---\n\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n\n---\n\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n[Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n\n### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n- What was tried: [specific approaches attempted]\n- Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n- Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n\n### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n- What worked: [successful approaches in this category]\n- Prefer for: [related questions where this category may help]\n\n---\n\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n[Approaches that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n- [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n\n---\n\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n[Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration]\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n[Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n\n---\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n- Max iterations: [from config]\n- Convergence threshold: [from config]\n- Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: true (default)\n- research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n- Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n- Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11\n- Canonical pause sentinel: `research/.deep-research-pause`\n- Capability matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n- Capability matrix doc: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n- Capability resolver: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`\n- Current generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n- Started: [timestamp]","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":118,"totalLines":118,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md","time":{"start":1781518688504,"end":1781518688512}},"id":"prt_ecac9dd8e001pbkrkQL0XEUx7c","sessionID":"ses_13537258affeVXgYvTahskeLzp","messageID":"msg_ecac9cc17001wsnCUXc5D1JTib"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781518688932,"sessionID":"ses_13537258affeVXgYvTahskeLzp","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"tool_URdXInzXa0mpnxOCYni1qJoJ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_dashboard.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_dashboard.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Dashboard Template\n3: description: Template for the auto-generated dashboard file regenerated after every iteration from JSONL + strategy data. Provides human-readable session overview and recovery surface.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep research dashboard\"\n6:   - \"research session overview\"\n7:   - \"research dashboard template\"\n8:   - \"research convergence trend\"\n9:   - \"research dead ends section\"\n10: importance_tier: normal\n11: contextType: general\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Deep Research Dashboard - Session Overview\n15: \n16: Auto-generated from JSONL state log and strategy file. Regenerated after every iteration evaluation. Never manually edited.\n17: \n18: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n19: \n20: ### Purpose\n21: \n22: Provides a compact, human-readable summary of the current research session. Serves three roles:\n23: 1. **Observability** — quick status check during long autonomous runs\n24: 2. **Recovery surface** — second recovery channel alongside JSONL after context compaction\n25: 3. **Lifecycle decision** — in confirm mode, shown before `resume` or `restart`\n26: \n27: ### Usage\n28: \n29: - **Location:** `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md`\n30: - **Generated by:** Orchestrator (step_generate_dashboard in YAML workflow)\n31: - **Data sources:** `deep-research-state.jsonl` + `findings-registry.json` + `deep-research-strategy.md`\n32: - **Protection:** `auto-generated` — overwritten each iteration, never manually edited\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ## 2. STATUS\n37: - Topic: [from config]\n38: - Started: [from config.createdAt]\n39: - Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n40: - Iteration: [N] of [maxIterations]\n41: - Session ID: [from config.lineage.sessionId]\n42: - Parent Session: [from config.lineage.parentSessionId or none]\n43: - Lifecycle Mode: [new | resume | restart]\n44: - Generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: ## 3. PROGRESS\n49: \n50: | # | Focus | Track | Ratio | Findings | Status |\n51: |---|-------|-------|-------|----------|--------|\n52: | [per iteration from JSONL] |\n53: \n54: - iterationsCompleted: [from findings registry metrics]\n55: - keyFindings: [from findings registry metrics]\n56: - openQuestions: [from findings registry metrics]\n57: - resolvedQuestions: [from findings registry metrics]\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## 4. QUESTIONS\n62: - Answered: [X/Y]\n63: - [x] Q1: [summary] (iteration N)\n64: - [ ] Q2: [remaining]\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ## 5. TREND\n69: - Last 3 ratios: [0.XX -> 0.XX -> 0.XX] [improving | stable | declining]\n70: - Stuck count: [N]\n71: - Guard violations: [none | list]\n72: - convergenceScore: [from reducer metrics]\n73: - coverageBySources: [from reducer metrics]\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## 6. DEAD ENDS\n78: - [approach]: [reason] (iteration N)\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## 7. NEXT FOCUS\n83: [from strategy.md \"Next Focus\" section]\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ## 8. ACTIVE RISKS\n88: - [guard violations, high stuck count, declining trend, etc.]\n89: - [migration events, reducer warnings, lifecycle conflicts]\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## 9. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n94: \n95: Reference snippet showing what a rendered dashboard looks like after iteration 5 of a 10-iteration run. Use this as a visual anchor when inspecting a live dashboard.\n96: \n97: ```markdown\n98: # Deep Research Dashboard - Session Overview\n99: \n100: ## 2. STATUS\n101: - Topic: OpenCode plugin loader resilience\n102: - Started: 2026-04-20T09:14:22+02:00\n103: - Status: ITERATING\n104: - Iteration: 5 of 10\n105: - Session ID: dr-20260420-091422\n106: - Parent Session: none\n107: - Lifecycle Mode: new\n108: - Generation: 1\n109: \n110: ## 3. PROGRESS\n111: \n112: | # | Focus                       | Track        | Ratio | Findings | Status     |\n113: |---|-----------------------------|--------------|-------|----------|------------|\n114: | 1 | Entry-point discovery rules | architecture | 0.82  | 4        | converging |\n115: | 2 | ESM vs CommonJS interop     | runtime      | 0.64  | 3        | converging |\n116: | 3 | Plugin-load error surfaces  | observability| 0.47  | 2        | converging |\n117: | 4 | Host/plugin version gating  | lifecycle    | 0.35  | 2        | converging |\n118: | 5 | Cross-runtime parity        | portability  | 0.28  | 1        | converging |\n119: \n120: ## 5. CONVERGENCE TREND\n121: - Last 3 ratios: 0.47 -> 0.35 -> 0.28 (declining)\n122: - Stuck count: 0\n123: - Guard violations: none\n124: - convergenceScore: 0.71\n125: - coverageBySources: 0.83\n126: ```\n\n(End of file - total 126 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Dashboard Template\ndescription: Template for the auto-generated dashboard file regenerated after every iteration from JSONL + strategy data. Provides human-readable session overview and recovery surface.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research dashboard\"\n  - \"research session overview\"\n  - \"research dashboard template\"\n  - \"research convergence trend\"\n  - \"research dead ends section\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\n---\n\n# Deep Research Dashboard - Session Overview\n\nAuto-generated from JSONL state log and strategy file. Regenerated after every iteration evaluation. Never manually edited.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_dashboard.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Dashboard Template\ndescription: Template for the auto-generated dashboard file regenerated after every iteration from JSONL + strategy data. Provides human-readable session overview and recovery surface.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research dashboard\"\n  - \"research session overview\"\n  - \"research dashboard template\"\n  - \"research convergence trend\"\n  - \"research dead ends section\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\n---\n\n# Deep Research Dashboard - Session Overview\n\nAuto-generated from JSONL state log and strategy file. Regenerated after every iteration evaluation. Never manually edited.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nProvides a compact, human-readable summary of the current research session. Serves three roles:\n1. **Observability** — quick status check during long autonomous runs\n2. **Recovery surface** — second recovery channel alongside JSONL after context compaction\n3. **Lifecycle decision** — in confirm mode, shown before `resume` or `restart`\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Location:** `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md`\n- **Generated by:** Orchestrator (step_generate_dashboard in YAML workflow)\n- **Data sources:** `deep-research-state.jsonl` + `findings-registry.json` + `deep-research-strategy.md`\n- **Protection:** `auto-generated` — overwritten each iteration, never manually edited\n\n---\n\n## 2. STATUS\n- Topic: [from config]\n- Started: [from config.createdAt]\n- Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n- Iteration: [N] of [maxIterations]\n- Session ID: [from config.lineage.sessionId]\n- Parent Session: [from config.lineage.parentSessionId or none]\n- Lifecycle Mode: [new | resume | restart]\n- Generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n\n---\n\n## 3. PROGRESS\n\n| # | Focus | Track | Ratio | Findings | Status |\n|---|-------|-------|-------|----------|--------|\n| [per iteration from JSONL] |\n\n- iterationsCompleted: [from findings registry metrics]\n- keyFindings: [from findings registry metrics]\n- openQuestions: [from findings registry metrics]\n- resolvedQuestions: [from findings registry metrics]\n\n---\n\n## 4. QUESTIONS\n- Answered: [X/Y]\n- [x] Q1: [summary] (iteration N)\n- [ ] Q2: [remaining]\n\n---\n\n## 5. TREND\n- Last 3 ratios: [0.XX -> 0.XX -> 0.XX] [improving | stable | declining]\n- Stuck count: [N]\n- Guard violations: [none | list]\n- convergenceScore: [from reducer metrics]\n- coverageBySources: [from reducer metrics]\n\n---\n\n## 6. DEAD ENDS\n- [approach]: [reason] (iteration N)\n\n---\n\n## 7. NEXT FOCUS\n[from strategy.md \"Next Focus\" section]\n\n---\n\n## 8. ACTIVE RISKS\n- [guard violations, high stuck count, declining trend, etc.]\n- [migration events, reducer warnings, lifecycle conflicts]\n\n---\n\n## 9. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n\nReference snippet showing what a rendered dashboard looks like after iteration 5 of a 10-iteration run. Use this as a visual anchor when inspecting a live dashboard.\n\n```markdown\n# Deep Research Dashboard - Session Overview\n\n## 2. STATUS\n- Topic: OpenCode plugin loader resilience\n- Started: 2026-04-20T09:14:22+02:00\n- Status: ITERATING\n- Iteration: 5 of 10\n- Session ID: dr-20260420-091422\n- Parent Session: none\n- Lifecycle Mode: new\n- Generation: 1\n\n## 3. PROGRESS\n\n| # | Focus                       | Track        | Ratio | Findings | Status     |\n|---|-----------------------------|--------------|-------|----------|------------|\n| 1 | Entry-point discovery rules | architecture | 0.82  | 4        | converging |\n| 2 | ESM vs CommonJS interop     | runtime      | 0.64  | 3        | converging |\n| 3 | Plugin-load error surfaces  | observability| 0.47  | 2        | converging |\n| 4 | Host/plugin version gating  | lifecycle    | 0.35  | 2        | converging |\n| 5 | Cross-runtime parity        | portability  | 0.28  | 1        | converging |\n\n## 5. CONVERGENCE TREND\n- Last 3 ratios: 0.47 -> 0.35 -> 0.28 (declining)\n- Stuck count: 0\n- Guard violations: none\n- convergenceScore: 0.71\n- coverageBySources: 0.83\n```","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":126,"totalLines":126,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_dashboard.md","time":{"start":1781518688928,"end":1781518688931}},"id":"prt_ecac9e0fa001kQbu7Tz1dx3Wsl","sessionID":"ses_13537258affeVXgYvTahskeLzp","messageID":"msg_ecac9cc17001wsnCUXc5D1JTib"}}
