{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781519015446,"sessionID":"ses_13537258affeVXgYvTahskeLzp","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"tool_WC4FduNiva7BQlaXlAu5aoZq","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/kimi-k2p7/deep-research-strategy.md","oldString":"## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n\n[None yet]\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n\n[To be populated by reducer]\n\n---\n\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n\n[To be populated by reducer]\n\n---\n\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n\n[To be populated by reducer]\n\n---\n\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n\n[To be populated by reducer]\n\n---\n\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n\nIteration 1: Systematically extract net-new mechanisms from `fable-mode-main/fable-mode.md` and `fable-mode-profile.md`, tagging each as doctrine/ritual/mechanism/measurement/model-specific and checking against Fable5.md + round 1.","newString":"## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n\n- [x] Q1: What net-new fable-5 techniques/rituals/mechanisms/measurements exist in fable-mode-main and opus-fable-mode-main vs Fable5.md and round 1? (fable-mode-main portion answered in iteration 1)\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n\n- Direct source-to-round-1 diff tagging worked: every finding from `fable-mode-profile.md` was checked against `Fable5.md` and `001-initial-refinement/implementation-summary.md`, giving a clean dedup column.\n- Categorizing each finding as doctrine/ritual/mechanism/measurement/model-specific made tiering signals obvious: most are Tier B mechanisms; voice/lexicon are Tier A doctrine.\n\n---\n\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n\n- Attempting to extract from `fable-mode-main/README.md` yielded only install instructions; not a useful source of doctrine.\n\n---\n\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n\n- Do not re-read `fable-mode-main/README.md` for mechanisms.\n\n---\n\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n\n- `fable-mode-main/README.md` is install-only; no doctrine to extract (iteration 1).\n- `fable-mode.md` command overlay is self-contained; no hidden mechanisms beyond the profile (iteration 1).\n\n---\n\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n\nIteration 2: Extract net-new mechanisms from `opus-fable-mode-main/` (`fable-mode.md`, `governor-block.md`, `leak_test.py`), with special attention to the recursion-control governor, output-shape rules, and the measurement harness."},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/kimi-k2p7/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/kimi-k2p7/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/kimi-k2p7/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -56,41 +56,43 @@\n ---\n \n ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n \n-[None yet]\n+- [x] Q1: What net-new fable-5 techniques/rituals/mechanisms/measurements exist in fable-mode-main and opus-fable-mode-main vs Fable5.md and round 1? (fable-mode-main portion answered in iteration 1)\n \n ---\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n \n ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n \n-[To be populated by reducer]\n+- Direct source-to-round-1 diff tagging worked: every finding from `fable-mode-profile.md` was checked against `Fable5.md` and `001-initial-refinement/implementation-summary.md`, giving a clean dedup column.\n+- Categorizing each finding as doctrine/ritual/mec