{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781519538294,"sessionID":"ses_13537258affeVXgYvTahskeLzp","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"tool_Ykc72Ha2okaZPscKJAIVfznT","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/kimi-k2p7/deep-research-strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/kimi-k2p7/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Strategy - Fable-5 Efficiency Surface Map (kimi-k2p7 lineage)\n3: description: Strategy and session tracking for the kimi-k2p7 fan-out lineage researching fable-mode and opus-fable-mode adjustable Public-repo surfaces.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"fable-5 efficiency research\"\n6:   - \"kimi-k2p7 lineage\"\n7:   - \"fable mode surface map\"\n8: importance_tier: normal\n9: contextType: planning\n10: ---\n11: \n12: # Deep Research Strategy - Fable-5 Efficiency Surface Map\n13: \n14: Lineage: `kimi-k2p7` | Session: `fanout-kimi-k2p7-1781518620710-yepc7q`\n15: \n16: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n17: \n18: ### Purpose\n19: \n20: Produce a ranked, tiered, sign-off-ready map of surface×delta recommendations that move any AI working in this repo toward fable-5 efficiency. The research is read-only this round: extract mechanisms, map adjustable Public-repo surfaces by runtime read-reliability, and score recommendations by leverage / (cost + blast-radius), all deduped against round 1's shipped set.\n21: \n22: ---\n23: \n24: ## 2. TOPIC\n25: \n26: Fable-5 efficiency — map every adjustable Public-repo surface and optimization from `external/fable-mode-main/` and `external/opus-fable-mode-main/`, deduped against round 1 (`001-initial-refinement`).\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n31: \n32: - [ ] Q3: Which surface×delta recommendations are highest leverage / lowest blast-radius, tiered A (doctrine text) / B (mechanisms: live-hook governor, recursion-control, lexicon/register split) / C (measurement: leak_test-style metric), and deduped vs round 1?\n33: - [ ] Q5: What are the risks, dependencies, and open questions for the top recommendations?\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n38: \n39: - No implementation this round; recommendations only.\n40: - No re-recommendation of round 1's shipped set (Operating Discipline subsection, `regression-baseline-and-delta.md`, `finding-is-a-hypothesis.md`, `main-branch-direct-push.md` 5th bullet, `sk-code/SKILL.md` baseline line).\n41: - No edits to framework surfaces.\n42: - No production testing or live dispatch.\n43: \n44: ---\n45: \n46: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n47: \n48: - Average newInfoRatio across the last 3 iterations falls below 0.05.\n49: - All 5 key questions answered with cited evidence.\n50: - Max 5 iterations reached.\n51: - Two consecutive iterations find no net-new mechanisms or surfaces.\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n56: \n57: - [x] Q1: What net-new fable-5 techniques/rituals/mechanisms/measurements exist in fable-mode-main and opus-fable-mode-main vs Fable5.md and round 1? (both source sets answered; 22 net-new findings, 2 partial overlaps)\n58: - [x] Q2: What adjustable Public-repo surfaces exist and what is their read-reliability per runtime? (8 surfaces mapped with read-reliability matrix)\n59: - [x] Q4: What concrete measurement surface can host a leak_test-style behavioral metric? (`/doctor` or `deep:model-benchmark`/`deep:skill-benchmark`; instrument transcript-derived metrics)\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n64: \n65: ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n66: \n67: - Direct source-to-round-1 diff tagging worked: every finding from `fable-mode-profile.md` was checked against `Fable5.md` and `001-initial-refinement/implementation-summary.md`, giving a clean dedup column.\n68: - Categorizing each finding as doctrine/ritual/mechanism/measurement/model-specific made tiering signals obvious: most are Tier B mechanisms; voice/lexicon are Tier A doctrine; measurement/execution mechanics are Tier C.\n69: - opus-fable-mode-main's `governor-block.md` is a ready-to-embed surface; `leak_test.py` is a ready-to-port harness.\n70: - Surface mapping by runtime read-reliability revealed that the `UserPromptSubmit` hook is the highest-leverage, lowest-blast mechanism surface because it is prompt-time, fail-open, and already wired across Claude/Codex/OpenCode.\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n75: \n76: - Attempting to extract from `fable-mode-main/README.md` yielded only install instructions; not a useful source of doctrine.\n77: - Attempting to extract from `opus-fable-mode-main/reinject.sh` yielded only a deployment helper; not a research mechanism.\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n82: \n83: - Do not re-read `fable-mode-main/README.md` for mechanisms.\n84: - Do not re-read `opus-fable-mode-main/reinject.sh` or `README.md` for mechanisms.\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n89: \n90: - `fable-mode-main/README.md` is install-only; no doctrine to extract (iteration 1).\n91: - `fable-mode.md` command overlay is self-contained; no hidden mechanisms beyond the profile (iteration 1).\n92: - `opus-fable-mode-main/reinject.sh` is a deployment helper, not a mechanism (iteration 2).\n93: - `opus-fable-mode-main/README.md` is install-only (iteration 2).\n94: - `opus-fable-mode-main/LICENSE` is not relevant to research (iteration 2).\n95: - `.opencode/commands/create/*.md` are scaffolding templates; not suitable for behavioral governor injection (iteration 3).\n96: - `Barter/ai-speckit/coder/AGENTS.md` git-posture contradiction is pre-existing and needs owner resolution before any fable-5 delta there (iteration 3).\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n101: \n102: Iteration 4: Build the ranked, tiered, deduped surface×delta recommendation map. Score each candidate by leverage / (cost + blast-radius), assign Tier A/B/C, and map to the best surface from iteration 3.\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n107: \n108: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n109: \n110: ### Round 1 shipped set (do NOT re-recommend)\n111: \n112: Round 1 (`001-initial-refinement`) distributed the distilled `Fable5.md` doctrine surgically:\n113: \n114: - `AGENTS.md` / `CLAUDE.md` §1 gained an `Operating Discipline — Claim Legibility & Blast-Radius` subsection (9 bullets): confirmed-vs-inferred claims, baseline before \"no regressions\" + report delta, finding-as-hypothesis until cited code is opened, scope lock, rollback before irreversible/outward actions, match effort to blast radius, name what still speaks the old contract.\n115: - Two new constitutional rules: `regression-baseline-and-delta.md` and `finding-is-a-hypothesis.md`.\n116: - `main-branch-direct-push.md` gained a 5th \"How to apply\" bullet for non-git outward/irreversible actions (deploy, send, migrate, overwrite shared state): name rollback, stop for yes.\n117: - `sk-code/SKILL.md` gained a \"Baseline & blast-radius\" line after the Iron Law.\n118: - Explicitly dropped: sk-git embedding (already covered), orchestrate.md §5 hard-checklist (superseded by constitutional rule), machine-checkable shared evidence contract (deferred follow-up).\n119: \n120: ### New sources for round 2\n121: \n122: 1. **`external/Fable5.md`** — distilled doctrine (already partially shipped): verify before claim, claim legibility, baseline+delta, finding-as-hypothesis, scope, rollback, match effort.\n123: \n124: 2. **`external/fable-mode-main/`** — a behavioral profile + command overlay:\n125:    - `fable-mode-profile.md`: forensic profile of Claude Fable 5 (62KB). Core conviction: expensive failures live where confirmation is cheapest to skip. Behaviors: recon before design, plan the turn, test-first with mutation check, verification ladder (unit → in-memory → on-server → live → headless), distrust own prior output, worst-first triage by downstream consequence, scope-frugal/process-expensive, fail-closed construction, scar-tissue curation, cold-successor handoff, turn rotting lists into self-auditing tests, reuse maps, single-event blast-radius lists, two-register voice (clipped colon-terminated while working; dense at turn boundaries), lexicon (pin, verify, trap, drift, deliberate, load-bearing, seam, byte-identical, fixpoint).\n126:    - `fable-mode.md`: command overlay that activates the persona temporarily. Guardrails: user's own instructions win; do not let process dwarf a small task.\n127: \n128: 3. **`external/opus-fable-mode-main/`** — a governor for Opus 4.8 + measurement harness:\n129:    - `fable-mode.md`: \"Reason about the problem and the person. Never about yourself.\" Recursion control: start claims later, stop earlier, one audit then done (depth limit 1), hand back genuine uncertainty. Output shape: minimum honest qualifier, commit decisions with `// DECISION:`, outcome over visible process. Orientation: look outward, lumpy bit not armor bit, reject wrong framings. Execution mechanics: batch tool calls (~4 actions per prose block), median ~18 words/msg, result-first openings.\n130:    - `governor-block.md`: shorter form of the same governor for permanent CLAUDE.md embedding.\n131:    - `leak_test.py`: measurement harness for Claude Code transcripts. Metrics: median words/message, tool:text ratio, unsolicited-caveat %, \"I'll/Let me\" opener %. Compares `opus_pre`, `opus_post`, `fable` buckets.\n132: \n133: ### Coverage note\n134: \n135: `resource-map.md` not present at init; skipping coverage gate.\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n140: \n141: - Max iterations: 5\n142: - Convergence threshold: 0.05\n143: - Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n144: - Progressive synthesis: true\n145: - research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n146: - Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n147: - Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11\n148: - Canonical pause sentinel: `.deep-research-pause`\n149: - Current generation: 1\n150: - Started: 2026-06-15T12:17:00Z\n\n(End of file - total 150 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy - Fable-5 Efficiency Surface Map (kimi-k2p7 lineage)\ndescription: Strategy and session tracking for the kimi-k2p7 fan-out lineage researching fable-mode and opus-fable-mode adjustable Public-repo surfaces.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"fable-5 efficiency research\"\n  - \"kimi-k2p7 lineage\"\n  - \"fable mode surface map\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Fable-5 Efficiency Surface Map\n\nLineage: `kimi-k2p7` | Session: `fanout-kimi-k2p7-1781518620710-yepc7q`\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nProduce a ranked, tiered, sign-off-ready map of surface×delta recommendations that move any AI working in this repo toward fable-5 efficiency. The research is read-only this round: extract mechanisms, map adjustable Public-repo surfaces by runtime read-reliability, and score recommendations by leverage / (cost + blast-radius), all deduped against round 1's shipped set.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/kimi-k2p7/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy - Fable-5 Efficiency Surface Map (kimi-k2p7 lineage)\ndescription: Strategy and session tracking for the kimi-k2p7 fan-out lineage researching fable-mode and opus-fable-mode adjustable Public-repo surfaces.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"fable-5 efficiency research\"\n  - \"kimi-k2p7 lineage\"\n  - \"fable mode surface map\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Fable-5 Efficiency Surface Map\n\nLineage: `kimi-k2p7` | Session: `fanout-kimi-k2p7-1781518620710-yepc7q`\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nProduce a ranked, tiered, sign-off-ready map of surface×delta recommendations that move any AI working in this repo toward fable-5 efficiency. The research is read-only this round: extract mechanisms, map adjustable Public-repo surfaces by runtime read-reliability, and score recommendations by leverage / (cost + blast-radius), all deduped against round 1's shipped set.\n\n---\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n\nFable-5 efficiency — map every adjustable Public-repo surface and optimization from `external/fable-mode-main/` and `external/opus-fable-mode-main/`, deduped against round 1 (`001-initial-refinement`).\n\n---\n\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n\n- [ ] Q3: Which surface×delta recommendations are highest leverage / lowest blast-radius, tiered A (doctrine text) / B (mechanisms: live-hook governor, recursion-control, lexicon/register split) / C (measurement: leak_test-style metric), and deduped vs round 1?\n- [ ] Q5: What are the risks, dependencies, and open questions for the top recommendations?\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n\n- No implementation this round; recommendations only.\n- No re-recommendation of round 1's shipped set (Operating Discipline subsection, `regression-baseline-and-delta.md`, `finding-is-a-hypothesis.md`, `main-branch-direct-push.md` 5th bullet, `sk-code/SKILL.md` baseline line).\n- No edits to framework surfaces.\n- No production testing or live dispatch.\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n\n- Average newInfoRatio across the last 3 iterations falls below 0.05.\n- All 5 key questions answered with cited evidence.\n- Max 5 iterations reached.\n- Two consecutive iterations find no net-new mechanisms or surfaces.\n\n---\n\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n\n- [x] Q1: What net-new fable-5 techniques/rituals/mechanisms/measurements exist in fable-mode-main and opus-fable-mode-main vs Fable5.md and round 1? (both source sets answered; 22 net-new findings, 2 partial overlaps)\n- [x] Q2: What adjustable Public-repo surfaces exist and what is their read-reliability per runtime? (8 surfaces mapped with read-reliability matrix)\n- [x] Q4: What concrete measurement surface can host a leak_test-style behavioral metric? (`/doctor` or `deep:model-benchmark`/`deep:skill-benchmark`; instrument transcript-derived metrics)\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n\n- Direct source-to-round-1 diff tagging worked: every finding from `fable-mode-profile.md` was checked against `Fable5.md` and `001-initial-refinement/implementation-summary.md`, giving a clean dedup column.\n- Categorizing each finding as doctrine/ritual/mechanism/measurement/model-specific made tiering signals obvious: most are Tier B mechanisms; voice/lexicon are Tier A doctrine; measurement/execution mechanics are Tier C.\n- opus-fable-mode-main's `governor-block.md` is a ready-to-embed surface; `leak_test.py` is a ready-to-port harness.\n- Surface mapping by runtime read-reliability revealed that the `UserPromptSubmit` hook is the highest-leverage, lowest-blast mechanism surface because it is prompt-time, fail-open, and already wired across Claude/Codex/OpenCode.\n\n---\n\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n\n- Attempting to extract from `fable-mode-main/README.md` yielded only install instructions; not a useful source of doctrine.\n- Attempting to extract from `opus-fable-mode-main/reinject.sh` yielded only a deployment helper; not a research mechanism.\n\n---\n\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n\n- Do not re-read `fable-mode-main/README.md` for mechanisms.\n- Do not re-read `opus-fable-mode-main/reinject.sh` or `README.md` for mechanisms.\n\n---\n\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n\n- `fable-mode-main/README.md` is install-only; no doctrine to extract (iteration 1).\n- `fable-mode.md` command overlay is self-contained; no hidden mechanisms beyond the profile (iteration 1).\n- `opus-fable-mode-main/reinject.sh` is a deployment helper, not a mechanism (iteration 2).\n- `opus-fable-mode-main/README.md` is install-only (iteration 2).\n- `opus-fable-mode-main/LICENSE` is not relevant to research (iteration 2).\n- `.opencode/commands/create/*.md` are scaffolding templates; not suitable for behavioral governor injection (iteration 3).\n- `Barter/ai-speckit/coder/AGENTS.md` git-posture contradiction is pre-existing and needs owner resolution before any fable-5 delta there (iteration 3).\n\n---\n\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n\nIteration 4: Build the ranked, tiered, deduped surface×delta recommendation map. Score each candidate by leverage / (cost + blast-radius), assign Tier A/B/C, and map to the best surface from iteration 3.\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n\n### Round 1 shipped set (do NOT re-recommend)\n\nRound 1 (`001-initial-refinement`) distributed the distilled `Fable5.md` doctrine surgically:\n\n- `AGENTS.md` / `CLAUDE.md` §1 gained an `Operating Discipline — Claim Legibility & Blast-Radius` subsection (9 bullets): confirmed-vs-inferred claims, baseline before \"no regressions\" + report delta, finding-as-hypothesis until cited code is opened, scope lock, rollback before irreversible/outward actions, match effort to blast radius, name what still speaks the old contract.\n- Two new constitutional rules: `regression-baseline-and-delta.md` and `finding-is-a-hypothesis.md`.\n- `main-branch-direct-push.md` gained a 5th \"How to apply\" bullet for non-git outward/irreversible actions (deploy, send, migrate, overwrite shared state): name rollback, stop for yes.\n- `sk-code/SKILL.md` gained a \"Baseline & blast-radius\" line after the Iron Law.\n- Explicitly dropped: sk-git embedding (already covered), orchestrate.md §5 hard-checklist (superseded by constitutional rule), machine-checkable shared evidence contract (deferred follow-up).\n\n### New sources for round 2\n\n1. **`external/Fable5.md`** — distilled doctrine (already partially shipped): verify before claim, claim legibility, baseline+delta, finding-as-hypothesis, scope, rollback, match effort.\n\n2. **`external/fable-mode-main/`** — a behavioral profile + command overlay:\n   - `fable-mode-profile.md`: forensic profile of Claude Fable 5 (62KB). Core conviction: expensive failures live where confirmation is cheapest to skip. Behaviors: recon before design, plan the turn, test-first with mutation check, verification ladder (unit → in-memory → on-server → live → headless), distrust own prior output, worst-first triage by downstream consequence, scope-frugal/process-expensive, fail-closed construction, scar-tissue curation, cold-successor handoff, turn rotting lists into self-auditing tests, reuse maps, single-event blast-radius lists, two-register voice (clipped colon-terminated while working; dense at turn boundaries), lexicon (pin, verify, trap, drift, deliberate, load-bearing, seam, byte-identical, fixpoint).\n   - `fable-mode.md`: command overlay that activates the persona temporarily. Guardrails: user's own instructions win; do not let process dwarf a small task.\n\n3. **`external/opus-fable-mode-main/`** — a governor for Opus 4.8 + measurement harness:\n   - `fable-mode.md`: \"Reason about the problem and the person. Never about yourself.\" Recursion control: start claims later, stop earlier, one audit then done (depth limit 1), hand back genuine uncertainty. Output shape: minimum honest qualifier, commit decisions with `// DECISION:`, outcome over visible process. Orientation: look outward, lumpy bit not armor bit, reject wrong framings. Execution mechanics: batch tool calls (~4 actions per prose block), median ~18 words/msg, result-first openings.\n   - `governor-block.md`: shorter form of the same governor for permanent CLAUDE.md embedding.\n   - `leak_test.py`: measurement harness for Claude Code transcripts. Metrics: median words/message, tool:text ratio, unsolicited-caveat %, \"I'll/Let me\" opener %. Compares `opus_pre`, `opus_post`, `fable` buckets.\n\n### Coverage note\n\n`resource-map.md` not present at init; skipping coverage gate.\n\n---\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n\n- Max iterations: 5\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05\n- Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: true\n- research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n- Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n- Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11\n- Canonical pause sentinel: `.deep-research-pause`\n- Current generation: 1\n- Started: 2026-06-15T12:17:00Z","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":150,"totalLines":150,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/149-operate-like-fable-5/002-fable-mode-efficiency-research/research/lineages/kimi-k2p7/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1781519538282,"end":1781519538292}},"id":"prt_ecad6d37c001IheGNuEIQB7bkc","sessionID":"ses_13537258affeVXgYvTahskeLzp","messageID":"msg_ecad6c131001fgM7nL9L5mMSTn"}}
